    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix f5star() function output for 5G AKA resynchronization\n\n### Summary\nThe f5star() function in the USIM AKA implementation was not producing the expected anonymity key during resynchronization procedures. This caused authentication failures when handling SQN synchronization in 5G networks.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/NAS/UE/API/USIM/aka_functions.c`: Modified f5star() to output the correct bytes according to 3GPP TS 35.206 specification\n\n### Reproduction\nWhen performing 5G AKA authentication with resynchronization, the AUTS parameter computation was failing because f5star() was outputting the same 6 bytes as f5() instead of the specified offset bytes. This led to incorrect SQNMS concealment values and authentication rejects from the network.\n\nNetwork operators reported increased authentication failure rates during UE re-attachment scenarios where resynchronization was required. The issue was particularly noticeable in roaming scenarios where SQN drift was more common.\n\n"
}